  "key_insight": "Adaptive threshold coupling can nullify HELIX control activation; decoupled frozen-threshold control restores actuated overrides.",
  "limitations": [
    "control restoration is strongest in-distribution and weakly transferable cross-distribution",
    "high override regimes can occur under transfer",
    "method is targeted to class-4 post-hoc control and does not retrain representation"
  ],
  "claim": "HELIX control behavior is governed by threshold\u2013margin coupling: online adaptive coupling induces inactivity, while frozen decoupling restores override controllability without retraining.",
